commitResults.messageBody:
1) renamed file back to Duke.
2) Added echo.
Added 3 subclasses of "Task" and added more 3 respective commands to Duke.
added test cases into input.txt and expected display results in EXPECTED.txt.

Added error handling for the following:
- empty descriptions for all relevant commands
- invalid formatting for "event" and "deadline" commands.
- non-numerical and out-of-bounds index for mark/unmark commands.
- unknown commands

Added "delete" function to remove a task from the list.

Added special message upon using "list" command on an empty list.

Switched the data type for storing the list of tasks to ArrayList.

- Added fileManager.java

Handles saving and writing of task list to tasks.csv file.

- Updated Duke.java to use fileManager to fetch task list (if any) from data.csv on initialize, and overwrites the csv file with update list on exit.

- Added an abstract function in Task.java to convert the task details into a string line to store in csv file. ToDo, Deadline and Event will provide their own implementations.

Updated Duke to recognize and parse date and time from input.

Added dateManager to handle parsing and output formatting of date and time.

Deadline and Event no longer holds their dates as a string, but as type "LocalDateTime".

Changed the structure of saving deadline and event types. Now it follows a fixed format of "dd MMM yyyy HH:mm".

Updated Duke to be more OOP friendly.

Added taskManager to manage task related actions, exclusding fetching and storing of task data in csv file. That is still being maintained by fileManager.

Added commandManager to parse input and separate it into command word and description. It then directs the description to the appropriate managers and forwards the responses to Response class.

Added Response.java to handle the outputs of the Duke bot. In particular, it handles the reading of input and passing it to commandManager, then formats and outputs the responses appropriately to the interface.

moved all files in "main/java" into new folder "someboty" and is treated as a package.

Changed the name of the bot from "Duke" to "someboty" (I know, very creative).

Merged A-Gradle branch to main branch  and set up gradle in Intellij.

Fixed the file path to tasks.csv file in fileManager. Now the path file is relative to root of project directory instead of current directory.

Added JUnit tests, specifically for "taskManager" and "dateManager".

"taskManagerTest" tests on correct parsing and formatting of newly created tasks, and ensuring that task list holds the correct number of tasks (i.e. use invalid index when deleting a task should not decrease or increase the task list).

"dateManagerTest" tests on correct parsing of valid and invalid date formats.

Improved OOP-ness of code, specifically moving the checking of task type and adding of new tasks from "taskManager" to "Task".

Packaged "someboty" app into a jar file and released version 0.1 (v0.1) on Github.

Changed the initial file path in "someBOTy" to be the current directory.

Added checking of existing directory "data" in current file path and create one if necessary.

Added "find" feature to allow user to find tasks that matches the given substring.

Changed return type of "addTask", "deleteTask" and "setTaskStatus" in "taskManager" to Task (previously String). The formatting of output string will now be handled in commandManager.

Fixed bug that causes the fileWriter to throw an error when trying to write to file.
Provided JavaDoc comments to most of the non-private (and some private) methods and classes.
Tweaked some code to comply with the coding standard.
